    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, if the asset loses value more quickly early on, you would use an accelerated method like the diminishing balance or units-of-production approach instead of straight-line. These methods handle varying usage patterns by calculating a higher depreciation expense in earlier years as consumption and wear and tear are greatest. While methods like double-declining balance can provide the increasing rate of depreciation you expect for high-use machinery, overestimating them or miscalculating them can lead to errors in your financial reports. Focus on choosing the method that best reflects how the asset's utility typically declines.",
